Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum front-rimmed a 3 as time expired, sending it to OT.
Payton Pritchard scored six points in overtime to lead the Celtics to a 108-104 win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The fast break was Boston's remedy, as the Celtics outscored the Nets 20-10 in transition.
Jrue Holiday added 17 points and five assists, and Derrick White scored 14 and had six assists for the Celtics.
Others: Cam Thomas reached 30 points for the fourth time this season, finishing with 31 to lead the Nets.

Cameron Johnson was fouled by Tatum after missing a wide open 3-point attempt in the closing seconds of regulation but grabbed his own miss. He calmly sank two free throws, tying it at 94 with 7.6 seconds to play.
